node.text:
For Screaming Vlog 36 we meet up with @salba69, @twistthewrist, @jake_wooten, and @catchsurf Pros @kalanirobb, @johnnyredmond, and @tylerstanaland at Catch Surf HQ in Encinitas, CA! Catch Surf’s @beefs_official gives us a bit of insight on the brand, and explains the similarities between SC and Catch Surf. With stoke searching in mind, we teamed up with Catch Surf to create a series of shred sticks that the crew got to put to the test! After drying off from the water, we go from the waves to the 'crete as the squad heads to Poods Park to catch a session before calling it a day! Hit up our @youtube channel to watch now! Where should we go in the next Screaming Vlog? Let us know in the comments!
🎥: @skyrar @beefs_official @trevarcushing
🎬: @trevarcushing
#SantaCruzSkateboards

For Screaming Vlog 35 we meet up with @tomasta, @k3vinbraun, @maurcoy, @jeremeknibbs, and SC Team Manager @instapizzle in San Diego while we keep the hype train rollin' celebrating @jake_wooten’s long awaited PRO status. From skating flat ground straight to the vert ramp, we gather the squad and head out to @tonyhawk’s compound to get some serious shredding dialed in. We got @twistthewrist, @ericdressen and @blood_wizard Pro @tweestopher in the mix to get things fired up while the gang hits every inch of The Birdman’s indoor skatepark! Where should we go in the next Screaming Vlog? Let us know in the comments!

Today we are stoked to talk about and put to the test the 8.375 x 32 @blakeular 'Beach Wolf' Pro Model Deck! This board features amazing artwork done by our friend @tallboy666! This one also has a 14.5 wheelbase for more stability. Be sure to stop by your local shop and see if they have this one available. We put Santa Cruz Skateboards Brand Manager @andrewcannon to the test with three different challenges to find out how this setup skates! Let us know in the comments below what challenges we should throw in the bins next!
👉 This weeks product setup:
8.375 x 32 @blakeular Pro ‘Beach Wolf’ Deck
149 Standard Stage 11 @independenttrucks
53mm 99A @rictawheels Chrome Cores 
@bronsonspeedco CERAMICS 🏁💨

Hit our @youtube channel at 10:00 AM PST to join the premiere & live chat with @tomasta for our latest installment of "What I'm Riding”! In this series we will be rapping out with your favorite members of the SC squad and dig in to their current setup to learn all about what is currently under their hood. What size board does Tom ride? How tight are his trucks? Does he pop his bearing shields?! All of these questions and much much more are answered in Episode 3 filmed by @thekillatapes and @trevarcushing! Who should we tap for our next episode? Let us know in the comments!
👉 Tom's Setup:
8.0 in x 31.5 in Tom Asta Cosmic Cat Dot (14.1 WB)
147 Thunder Hollow Lights
MOB Grip
52mm 99a Tom Asta Signature Ricta Wheels
Bronson Ceramics
Diamond 7/8ths Allen Hardware
🗣 Swipe up in our story for link to premiere, see you there!
🎬: @tylerlodzinski
#SantaCruzSkateboards

node.text:
Today we are hyped to talk about and put to the test the 8.0 x 31.6 Rad Dot Deck! This board features artwork by our friend Thomas Fernández aka @liveradstudios based off of the original #JimPhillips Classic Dot graphic! Be sure to stop by your local shop and see if they have this one available. We put Santa Cruz Skateboards Brand Manager @andrewcannon to the test with three different challenges to find out how this setup skates! Hit up our @youtube channel to watch now, then let us know in the comments below what challenges we should throw in the bins next! 
👉 This weeks product setup:
8.0 x 31.6 ‘Rad Dot’ Deck
139 Standard Stage 11 @independenttrucks
53mm 99A @rictawheels Speed Rings
@bronsonspeedco G3s
7/8ths Indy Allen Bolts
Some FUN Mandala Hand Clear @mobgrip 🎯
🎥: @ericdanescu
#SantaCruzSkateboards
